11. Pañcagatipeyyālavagga Pettidevapettivisayasutta ^n1201 … “Evameva kho, bhikkhave, appakā te sattā ye pettivisayā cutā devesu paccājāyanti; atha kho eteva bahutarā sattā ye pettivisayā cutā pettivisaye paccājāyanti. 
Taṁ kissa hetu? 
Adiṭṭhattā, bhikkhave, catunnaṁ ariyasaccānaṁ. 
Katamesaṁ catunnaṁ? 
Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa, dukkhasamudayassa ariyasaccassa, dukkhanirodhassa ariyasaccassa, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa. 
Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṁ dukkha’nti yogo karaṇīyo, ‘ayaṁ dukkhasamudayo’ti yogo karaṇīyo, ‘ayaṁ dukkhanirodho’ti yogo karaṇīyo, ‘ayaṁ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. 
Idamavoca bhagavā. 
Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṁ abhinandunti. 
Tiṁsatimaṁ. 
Pañcagatipeyyālavaggo ekādasamo. 
Tassuddānaṁ 
Manussato cutā chāpi, 
devā cutā nirayato; 
Tiracchānapettivisayā, 
tiṁsamatto gativaggoti. 
Saccasaṁyuttaṁ dvādasamaṁ. 
Mahāvaggo pañcamo. 
Tassuddānaṁ 
Maggabojjhaṅgaṁ satiyā, 
indriyaṁ sammappadhānaṁ; 
Baliddhipādānuruddhā, 
jhānānāpānasaṁyutaṁ; 
Sotāpatti saccañcāti, 
mahāvaggoti vuccatīti. 
Mahāvaggasaṁyuttapāḷi niṭṭhitā. 
Saṁyuttanikāyo samatto. 